EX6

1 Install and verify your tools
You only need two things:
java -version     # should print Java 11 or later
gradle -v         # should print a Gradle version
If either command isn’t found:
Java: install from https://adoptium.net
Gradle: install from https://gradle.org/install/ and add <gradle-home>\bin to PATH.

2. Create a New Gradle Java Project
You can do this using command prompt or manually.
Using Gradle command
gradle init --type java-application

Write a Custom build.gradle Script
Create a file named build.gradle in the project root:
plugins {
    id 'java'
    id 'application'
}

group = 'com.example'
version = '1.0-SNAPSHOT'

repositories {
    mavenCentral()
}

dependencies {
    testImplementation 'junit:junit:4.13.2'
}

application {
    // Set your main class here
    mainClass = 'com.example.App'
}

tasks.register('helloTask') {
    doLast {
        println ' Custom Gradle Task is running!'
    }
}

tasks.jar {
    manifest {
        attributes(
            'Main-Class': 'com.example.App'
        )
    }
}


5. Build the Project
In Command Prompt/Terminal:
Navigate your project
gradle build
You'll see:
BUILD SUCCESSFUL
JAR file will be located in:
build/libs/gradle-demo-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

 6. Run the Application
Option A: Using Gradle (Recommended)
gradle run


7. Run Custom Task Created in Script
gradle helloTask
Output:
 Custom Gradle Task is running!
